<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
On Monday night, a raid was conducted by about 150 players from Albion, in an attempt to seize control of Midgard's keep in the Frontier Lands.<BR>It was my first experience, and I have to admit I was truly dissapointed by one important aspect. It was an archer's/caster's fight. As a paladin, I had no fun whatsoever, being unable to wield a bow or crossbow. The best I could do was stand back and try to make myself small for my ennemy's arrows. <P>Perhpas I am wrong (God, do I hope so) but I think I may have chosen the worse possible class for realm vs. realm combat.<BR>It seems almost impossible to storm a keep (as of yet, at least) and my paladain's inability to wield a bow, made it no fun at all for me...<P>I think this sort of combat is way too dependant on archer's and having no ranged attack whatsoever as a paladin, well hard to play a part.<P>I also have to point out that as a tank, paladin's should be able to pull for their group, but surgical pulling without a ranged attack is suicidal...<P>Any thoughts?
</FONT>
